<div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent"><br />How many typical NES style songs can one fit in a 16 KB bank of UNROM or S*ROM?<br /></div><br />The driver is 3.4 kB, and a typical NES song (my enl_end.nsf in this case) uses about 3 kB (DPCM samples excluded).<br /><br />I don't think the music format is a big problem.<br />The driver would need some optimizations though, but mostly to decrease the CPU usage. I haven't really focused that much on the driver this far, as the goal has been getting the tracker usable, but it's probably time for that now.<br /><br />(Everything is open source, contributions are welcome)<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=28">jsr</a> — Tue Feb 07, 2006 1:02 pm</p><hr />
